President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Ron McCray as a member of the Federal Retirement Thrift Investment Board and Arnold F. Stancell as a member of the National Science Board, National Science Foundation. He also intends to appoint Matt Desch, Joseph E. Fergus, and Larissa Herda as members of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee. Ron McCray is a private investor and corporate director, Arnold F. Stancell is an Emeritus Professor, Matt Desch is the CEO of Iridium Communications Inc., Joseph E. Fergus is the founder and CEO of Communication Technologies, Inc., and Larissa Herda is the Chair CEO and President of tw telecom inc.